2026-01-26T19:40:52.542978Z  INFO codex_core::stream_events_utils: ToolCall: shell_command {"command":"cat <<'EOF' > /Users/duhl/git/ui/AGENTS.md\n# Repository Guidelines\n\n## Project Structure & Module Organization\n- `apps/` contains product surfaces: `org/`, `donor/`, `builder/`, and `storybook/`.\n- `packages/` holds shared libraries: `ui/` (core components), `utils/`, `form/`, `feature-flags/`, `api-client/`, `shared-types/`, and config packages (`config-jest`, `config-tailwind`, `config-typescript`).\n- `scripts/` includes local tooling such as the dev launcher (`./scripts/dev`) and setup (`./scripts/setup.sh`).\n- Root configs include `biome.jsonc`, `turbo.json`, and `pnpm-workspace.yaml`.\n\n## Build, Test, and Development Commands\n- `pnpm dev` runs the monorepo dev workflow (clears ports 3200–3299 and starts app dev servers).\n- `pnpm build` builds all workspaces with Turbo.\n- `pnpm test` runs workspace tests (Vitest/Jest depending on package).\n- `pnpm test-storybook` runs Storybook tests for the `apps/storybook` workspace.\n- `pnpm lint` runs Biome checks; `pnpm lint:fix` applies auto-fixes.\n- `pnpm typecheck` runs TypeScript checks across the repo.\n- `./scripts/setup.sh` provisions local deps (Node, pnpm, Nginx, SSL) and writes `.env`.\n\n## Coding Style & Naming Conventions\n- Formatting and linting are enforced by Biome; prefer running `pnpm lint:fix` before pushing.\n- Use Tailwind semantic tokens (for example `bg-primary`, `text-muted-foreground`) instead of raw colors; variables are defined under `packages/ui/src/styles.css`.\n- Component work lives in `packages/ui/src/components`, with co-located stories and tests.\n- Branch naming follows `[username]/[feature-description]` (from `README.md`).\n\n## Testing Guidelines\n- Primary unit testing uses Vitest; some packages (for example `packages/feature-flags`) still use Jest.\n- Test files follow `*.test.ts` or `*.test.tsx` naming in the same folder as the module.\n- Run focused tests with `pnpm --filter <workspace> test` when iterating locally.\n\n## Commit & Pull Request Guidelines\n- Commit messages in history are mostly conventional: `type(scope): subject` (for example `feat(org): add import action`).\n- Some older commits use `feature(scope): ...`, but new work should follow the conventional format in `CONTRIBUTING.md`.\n- GPG-signed commits are required for this repo.\n- PRs should include a clear description, list the commands run, and attach screenshots or Storybook links for UI changes.\n\n## Configuration & Local Services\n- Local dev expects Docker and uses Nginx/SSL for `*.anedot.me` domains; see `SETUP.md` for host and cert details.\nEOF","workdir":"/Users/duhl/git/ui"}
