2026-01-28T14:11:55.625219Z  INFO codex_core::stream_events_utils: ToolCall: shell_command {"command":"cat <<'EOF' > /Users/duhl/git/anedot-frontend/lead_1.md\n# Lead Pages – Public Render Inventory + Data Complexity\n\n## Scope\nPublic render of lead pages (not the builder UI). Primary entry is the public action page route that renders `pageType: 'lead'`.\n\n## Entry points & routing\n- `src/pages/ActionPages/pages/PublicActionPage/PublicActionPage.tsx`\n  - Route config for `/:accountSlug/:actionPageSlug`, `/:actionPageSlug`, plus receipt routes.\n  - Wraps the public view with `FeaturedVideoWrapper` and redirects legacy event URLs.\n- `src/pages/ActionPages/pages/PublicActionPage/ActionPageView/ActionPageView.tsx`\n  - Fetches action page data via `useShowActionPage` and decides between event vs. regular render.\n  - Sets favicon from `actionPage`/account.\n\n## Data fetching & server interaction\n- `src/state/action_pages/queries/useShowActionPage.ts`\n  - GET `/public/action_pages/:actionPageSlug?account_slug=...&custom_domain=...`\n  - `custom_domain` path uses `window.location.hostname` when `accountSlug` is absent.\n- `src/pages/ActionPages/pages/PublicActionPage/ActionPageView/ActionPageLayout/ActionPageBody/hooks/useActionPageBody.ts`\n  - **Core orchestration**: initial values, schema, amounts, timers, upsells, upgrades, analytics, and submission.\n  - Uses `useActionPagePaymentSubmission` for submit flow.\n  - Dynamically derives fund overrides and amounts from query params.\n- `src/state/action_pages/mutations/useActionPagePaymentSubmission.ts`\n  - Orchestrates payment processing (sub-payment flow) and submission.\n- `src/state/action_pages/mutations/useSubmitActionPage.ts`\n  - POST `/public/submissions/:type` (type is `donation`, `lead`, `event`, `storefront` or `donation_auth`).\n\n## Main render tree (public lead page)\n- `ActionPageView` → `ActionPageLayout` → `ActionPageBody` → `ActionPageFormPresentation`\n- **Layout**: `ActionPageBackground`, `ActionPageHeader`, `ActionPageFooter`, `ActionPageInfo`, SEO/twitter/x-pixel scripts.\n- **Form**: `ActionPageFormBlock` → `ActionPageForm` → `StandardFields` + `CustomField`/`LoadableCustomField`.\n- **Payment/Submit**: `ActionPagePaymentBlock` (lead pages skip the payment method UI, but still render the submit button).\n\n## Validation & schema\n- `src/pages/ActionPages/pages/PublicActionPage/ActionPageView/hooks/useActionPageSchema/useActionPageSchema.ts`\n  - Yup schema composition driven by `fieldConfiguration` and page type.\n  - Lead pages still require name/email/phone/address rules depending on configuration.\n\n## Submission + upgrade logic (high complexity)\n- `useActionPageBody` in `ActionPageBody/hooks`:\n  - **Pre-conversion upsell** logic (mostly donation pages, but still flows through the same hook).\n  - **Upgrade chain** logic (post-conversion upsells) controls upgrade pages and receipt navigation.\n  - **Submission type override**: lead submissions can become `donation` if allocations exist.\n  - **Analytics** logging via `useAnalytics` (GA/FB pixels, ecommerce tracking).\n  - **Turnstile/Kount** risk/anti-abuse integrations.\n  - **Embedded vs. full page** behaviors (iframe postMessage, callback URLs).\n\n## Components to inspect (public lead render)\n### Core routing + view\n- `src/pages/ActionPages/pages/PublicActionPage/PublicActionPage.tsx`\n- `src/pages/ActionPages/pages/PublicActionPage/ActionPageView/ActionPageView.tsx`\n\n### Layout & chrome\n- `src/pages/ActionPages/pages/PublicActionPage/ActionPageView/ActionPageLayout/ActionPageLayout.tsx`\n- `src/pages/ActionPages/pages/PublicActionPage/ActionPageView/ActionPageLayout/ActionPageBackground/`\n- `src/pages/ActionPages/pages/PublicActionPage/ActionPageView/ActionPageLayout/ActionPageHeader/`\n- `src/pages/ActionPages/pages/PublicActionPage/ActionPageView/ActionPageLayout/ActionPageFooter/`\n- `src/pages/ActionPages/pages/PublicActionPage/ActionPageView/ActionPageLayout/ActionPageInfo/`\n- `src/pages/ActionPages/pages/PublicActionPage/ActionPageView/ActionPageLayout/ActionPageSEO/`\n- `src/pages/ActionPages/pages/PublicActionPage/ActionPageView/ActionPageLayout/ActionPageXPixel/`\n\n### Body + orchestration\n- `src/pages/ActionPages/pages/PublicActionPage/ActionPageView/ActionPageLayout/ActionPageBody/ActionPageBody.tsx`\n- `src/pages/ActionPages/pages/PublicActionPage/ActionPageView/ActionPageLayout/ActionPageBody/hooks/useActionPageBody.ts`\n- `src/pages/ActionPages/pages/PublicActionPage/ActionPageView/ActionPageLayout/ActionPageBody/utils/getTimers.ts`\n\n### Form & fields\n- `src/pages/ActionPages/pages/PublicActionPage/ActionPageView/ActionPageLayout/ActionPageBody/ActionPageFormPresentation/ActionPageFormPresentation.tsx`\n- `src/pages/ActionPages/pages/PublicActionPage/ActionPageView/ActionPageLayout/ActionPageBody/ActionPageFormBlock/ActionPageFormBlock.tsx`\n- `src/pages/ActionPages/pages/ActionPagesBuilder/components/ActionPage/ActionPageForm/ActionPageForm.tsx`\n- `src/pages/ActionPages/pages/ActionPagesBuilder/components/ActionPage/ActionPageForm/Fields/StandardFields/StandardFields.tsx`\n- `src/pages/ActionPages/pages/ActionPagesBuilder/components/ActionPage/ActionPageForm/Fields/StandardFields/NameField/`\n- `src/pages/ActionPages/pages/ActionPagesBuilder/components/ActionPage/ActionPageForm/Fields/StandardFields/EmailField/`\n- `src/pages/ActionPages/pages/ActionPagesBuilder/components/ActionPage/ActionPageForm/Fields/StandardFields/PhoneField/`\n- `src/pages/ActionPages/pages/ActionPagesBuilder/components/ActionPage/ActionPageForm/Fields/StandardFields/AddressField/`\n- `src/pages/ActionPages/pages/ActionPagesBuilder/components/ActionPage/ActionPageForm/Fields/StandardFields/EmploymentField/`\n- `src/pages/ActionPages/pages/ActionPagesBuilder/components/ActionPage/ActionPageForm/Fields/StandardFields/MakeDonationAsSection/`\n- `src/ui/components/formControls/compositions/CustomField/`\n- `src/pages/Finance/pages/Commitments/components/ViewCommitmentDrawer/components/CustomFieldsSection/components/LoadableCustomField/`\n\n### Submit + payment UI\n- `src/pages/ActionPages/pages/PublicActionPage/ActionPageView/ActionPageLayout/ActionPageBody/ActionPagePaymentBlock/ActionPagePaymentBlock.tsx`\n- `src/ui/components/organisms/ActionPages/ActionPageSubmitButton/`\n- `src/ui/components/formControls/compositions/PaymentMethodForm/` (mostly donation pages; lead skips)\n\n### Analytics + security/risk\n- `src/pages/ActionPages/pages/PublicActionPage/ActionPageView/hooks/useAnalytics/`\n- `src/pages/ActionPages/pages/PublicActionPage/ActionPageView/ActionPageLayout/ActionPageBody/TurnstileChallenge/`\n- `src/pages/ActionPages/pages/PublicActionPage/ActionPageView/ActionPageLayout/ActionPageBody/hooks/useTurnstile.ts`\n\n## Notes for extraction\n- Lead pages share most public action page infrastructure with donation pages; payment UI is conditional on `isDonationPage`.\n- Form config and validation are tightly coupled to `PublicActionPage.fieldConfiguration` and `customFieldPositionsAttributes`.\n- Submission pipeline is intertwined with upgrades/upsells and uses a shared payment submission flow; you may want to isolate a lean path for `pageType: 'lead'`.\n- The public render uses a mix of `src/pages/...` and `src/ui/...` components, so component ownership is split across layers.\nEOF","workdir":"/Users/duhl/git/anedot-frontend"}
